suggested curriculum? 
Phase 1 - Foundations
	Start with Tanenbaum & van Steen chapters 1-5 (architecture, processes, communication)
	Read Lamport's "Time, Clocks..." paper
	Skim Kleppmann chapters 1-4 (foundations, data models, storage)
Phase 2 - Core Distributed Concepts
	Tanenbaum chapters 6-8 (synchronization, consistency, fault tolerance)
	Kleppmann chapters 5-9 (replication, partitioning, transactions, consistency)
	FLP and CAP theorem papers
	Raft paper + visualization
Phase 3 - Distributed OS Specifics
	Amoeba papers (all three listed above)
	Mach paper + comparison paper
	Tanenbaum's DOS survey paper
	Study microkernel vs monolithic debates
Phase 4 - Modern Systems
	Kleppmann chapters 10-12 (batch/stream processing)
	Chubby, ZooKeeper, Spanner papers
	MIT 6.824 labs (hands-on implementation)
